can raise your hand on Zoom, and I could just call on you. Or you could also put questions

00:00:55.160 --> 00:00:59.480
into the Zoom chat. And if you want me to read them out loud instead of you, you can

00:00:59.480 --> 00:01:06.519
just put a little star next to your question too. But I do like to reiterate, we want to

00:01:06.519 --> 00:01:11.320
hear from everybody, no matter your level of experience or the industry that you work

00:01:11.320 --> 00:01:19.199
in. So feel free to use the chat there, ask questions any way that works for you. But

00:01:19.199 --> 00:01:26.160
I am so happy to be joined by my co-host for today, Joseph Korsen. And Joseph, I might

00:01:26.160 --> 00:01:33.120
need a lesson in saying your last name. Manager of Data Science at Procogia. And Joseph, I'd

00:01:33.120 --> 00:01:37.199
love to have you introduce yourself and maybe share a little bit about the work that you do.

00:01:38.000 --> 00:01:42.559
Sure. Well, thank you for having me, Rachel. Happy to be here, and thank you all for joining

00:01:42.559 --> 00:01:47.760
as well. Yeah, my name is Joe. You did pronounce my last name correctly. It is Korsen.

00:01:49.360 --> 00:01:54.320
