Thank you. I see Robert put a question into the chat off the bat. This is one we used to ask in

00:03:24.479 --> 00:03:30.080
the beginning. So what are you super excited about right now in data science?

00:03:31.759 --> 00:03:37.039
Well, just kind of the opportunities, right? There are so many problems in the world that

00:03:37.039 --> 00:03:44.479
data science can solve, whether that be supply chain, cancer research. There's a lot of

00:03:44.479 --> 00:03:48.800
improvements that can be made in the world today. And I think that comes through automation

00:03:48.800 --> 00:03:52.240
initiatives, but eventually you need an understanding of the data set in itself.

00:03:53.199 --> 00:03:59.440
So first and foremost, I think we identify a problem. We look for a little bit of a solution

00:03:59.440 --> 00:04:04.080
to the problem and then kind of let that be self-sufficient, right? So I think it has a

00:04:04.080 --> 00:04:10.880
lot of opportunity to help. Awesome. Sam, I know you put a question to the chat.

00:04:11.679 --> 00:04:17.839
If you want to jump in and ask that live. Hey, Joseph, just a quick question. So what led you

00:04:17.839 --> 00:04:22.000
