Last year, I believe we doubled in size. We're on a similar pace this year. So I imagine that

00:05:18.959 --> 00:05:25.519
kind of reduces over time, but for now, that's the total. Can I ask you, how do you

00:05:26.160 --> 00:05:32.239
manage professional development and keep track with 16 different people?

00:05:34.079 --> 00:05:39.119
So it's a little bit challenging, but I think you kind of face similar challenges with smaller

00:05:39.119 --> 00:05:44.720
sized teams as well, right? So with a smaller firm, we are kind of considered a startup. So for

00:05:44.720 --> 00:05:50.640
the most part, it brings about more opportunity. So more senior people, they look for more of those

00:05:50.640 --> 00:05:56.640
leadership roles, those tech lead roles as well. There's kind of a mix between that batch, but

00:05:57.200 --> 00:06:02.720
for the most part, the more junior analysts or data scientists, they all have a little bit of

00:06:02.720 --> 00:06:08.880
a pain point where they need to develop, round out some skills. For me, I try to see where

